**Policy
	Every Shell Company:
	Has a systematic approach to HSSE & SP management designed to ensure compliance with the law and to achieve continuous performance improvement;
	Sets targets for improvement and measures, appraises and reports performance;
	Requires Contractors to manage HSSE & SP in line with this policy;
	Requires joint ventures under its operational control to apply this policy, and uses its
influence to promote it in its other ventures;
	Engages effectively with neighbors and impacted communities; and
	Includes HSSE performance in the appraisal of staff and rewards accordingly.

The HSSE Management System is designed to ensure compliance with the law and to achieve continuous performance improvement.

The HSSE policy is implemented through Shell's Management System, which is designed to identify and manage risk. Although the Pittsburg facility is not subject to Californias Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) Process Safety Management requirements, Shell has developed several similar procedures to protect the health and safety of their workers, the public, and the environment. The following summarizes portions of the Management System that are most closely aligned with OSHA's Process Safety Management requirements:

